          "narrative": "The pesticide risk condition in 2021 and 2022 indicates 95.2% and 96% of aquatic species, respectively, were unlikely to experience harmful effects from pesticides. There is therefore little if any change from the baseline condition. While this result represents the overall risk for all catchments in this region, some catchments had a much lower level of protection and will require considerably larger improvements to meet the target. In 2022, the Daintree, Barron and Murray catchments experienced a lower risk than the Wet Tropics region as a whole, while the Mulgrave-Russell, Johnstone, Tully and Herbert catchments experienced a higher risk. The improvement reported for the Tully catchment in 2020 was not evident in 2021 and 2022. Monitoring recommenced in the Mossman catchment which experienced a higher risk compared to when it was last monitored in 2019.",
